- Navigate to Vsphere home page. 
- Click on VM & Template. 
- Select a VM and Right Click Go to Rename.
- Rename your VM and Click on Ok
- As you can see Virtual Machine is Successfully Renamed.
- Now go back to home page of Vsphere. 
- Go to VM & Template and Select and Scroll down and Click on Edit Settings.
- Modify Your Hard Disk According to requirement and Click on Ok.
- As you can see here we Successfully Increased Storage Space. 
- Again Click on Edit Settings to Edit Memory. 
- Now Modify Your Memory According to Requirement.
